<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the specified server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Create the directory <code>lab13</code> in your <code>labs</code> directory, then move to it. 
    </li>

    <li>
	Perform LAB 10.1, 10.2, 10.3, 10.4 and LAB 10.5 [Exercises 1 &amp; 2].
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/9e/Labs/PDFs/LM_Chapter10_9e.pdf">Chapter 10 Lab</a>
	in the file <code>Lab13answers.txt</code>
	locating it in directory <code>lab13</code></li>. Then submit the file to your Lab 13 D2L Assignment dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, your name, assignment category &amp; number [e.g. Lab 13],
	and date must be included at the top of your file.
    </li>

    <li>
    When you are sure that each program is working correctly, use the <code>script</code> command to display first the source file, then execution, 
    of each lab assignment program.  The <code><b>^D</b></code> character will end the <code>script</code> session.<br>
    What you enter into your <code>script</code> session will look like this:
    <code>
	<pre>
	&gt;script -a Lab13typescript.txt
	&gt;g++ -std=c++11 -o &lt;program1&gt; &lt;program1&gt;.cpp
	&gt;program1
	    (your input to &lt;program1&gt; is here (if any))
	&gt;g++ -std=c++11 -o &lt;program2&gt; &lt;program2&gt;.cpp
	&gt;program2
	    (your input to &lt;program2&gt; is here (if any)))
		.
		 .
		  .
	&gt;^D
	</pre>
    </code>
    Submit <code>Lab13typescript.txt</code> to the Lab 13 D2L Assignment dropbox.<br>
    Also, submit to your Lab 13 D2L Assignment dropbox a syntax-highlighted PDF file for each source code that you execute and test in your script session.<br>
    Each PDF file should have the same name as the source file with the exception of the file extension (<code>.gpp</code> &rarr; <code>.pdf</code>).
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
